24:02.640 --> 24:07.580
The Science Fiction author Gene Wolfe is probably best known for his fascinating four-volume series, The Book of the New Sun.

24:07.940 --> 24:09.940
He also writes fine short stories in novellas.

24:10.440 --> 24:13.040
Two collections of his shorter fiction have been published so far,

24:13.480 --> 24:17.760
The Island of Doctor Death and Other Stories and Other Stories, and Gene Wolfe's Book of Days.

24:18.260 --> 24:20.780
There are some interesting facts surrounding one of his shorter pieces,

24:21.160 --> 24:22.860
The Island of Doctor Death and Other Stories.

24:22.860 --> 24:28.020
It's about a boy named Taki, who's reading a science fiction story entitled, The Island of Doctor Death.

24:28.460 --> 24:32.200
He becomes so enthralled by the story, and his own existence is so unattractive to him,

24:32.560 --> 24:35.760
that the characters in the narrative leave the story and become part of his real life.

24:36.120 --> 24:40.740
One of the interesting facts concerning the story is that it's written in the very rare second-person point of view.

24:40.940 --> 24:42.380
We asked Wolfe why he wrote it that way.

24:43.280 --> 24:47.540
I think largely as an experiment, I wanted to see if it could be done.

24:47.540 --> 25:00.660
I needed a very distinct way of setting off the material in the book, The Island of Doctor Death,

25:00.900 --> 25:07.100
which is the book that the boy Taki is reading in the story, from Taki's own story.

25:07.100 --> 25:18.280
And that was the strongest way of contrasting the two elements that I could come up with.

25:18.520 --> 25:27.080
I needed the very strong contrast in order to get the shock effect when the characters from the book that Taki was reading

25:27.080 --> 25:33.060
actually appeared in his own life, Captain Ransom and Doctor Death himself and so forth.

25:34.060 --> 25:37.320
One of the themes of the story is the difference between fantasy and reality.

25:37.720 --> 25:40.340
We asked Wolfe if he meant for the reader to choose one or the other.

25:41.080 --> 25:54.180
No, what I was trying to say, I think, was that the kind of literature that people tend perhaps to criticize children for having and reading

25:54.180 --> 26:05.800
is actually healthier and more straightforward in most cases than the world in which the children are actually living.

26:06.740 --> 26:17.740
So I took this The Island with the monster race, the ancient monster race and the mad scientist and so forth,

26:17.740 --> 26:27.360
and contrasted that with Taki's actual life experience with his mother and the mother's boyfriend and the party and so forth.

26:34.100 --> 26:39.320
Another interesting fact about The Island of Doctor Death and other stories is the two stories that Wolfe wrote soon afterwards.

26:40.120 --> 26:44.400
One is entitled The Death of Doctor Island and the other is called The Doctor of Death Island.

26:44.660 --> 26:46.420
We asked Wolfe why he wrote these other two.

26:46.420 --> 26:59.680
I get the mixed up myself. The Death of Doctor Island was simply that I was talking to Joe Hensley and The Island of Doctor Death and other stories had lost,

26:59.780 --> 27:09.640
pardon me, The Island of Doctor Death and other stories, had lost the nebula and it had lost to no award.

27:09.640 --> 27:17.020
So I started to see on the history and the history of science fiction writers of America to lose that award, to no award.

27:18.120 --> 27:24.460
Joe Hensley said, you should write one called The Death of Doctor Island and that would win now for sure.

27:25.300 --> 27:31.220
And he said that this is a joke of course. And I thought, well, he thinks I can't do it and I thought I can do it.

27:31.220 --> 27:43.600
So I started thinking about what kind of a story would go with that title, who Doctor Island might be and what the Death of Doctor Island might be and so forth.

27:44.060 --> 27:45.260
And came up with that story.

27:46.080 --> 27:48.820
And then why did he go on to write The Doctor of Death Island?

27:49.400 --> 28:00.560
Well, I wanted to see if I could do it again. People kept coming up to me and giving me various switches on that title because the business with the titles got a number of people fancied.

28:00.560 --> 28:13.160
And so I thought, well, I'll try it again and see if I can do it a third time. And I could. But it was sufficiently difficult that I didn't get terribly interested in trying to do it a fourth time.

